{"id":4876,"date":"2023-09-28T10:30:34","date_gmt":"2023-09-28T02:30:34","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/192.168.8.150\/wordpress\/?page_id=4876"},"modified":"2023-12-21T10:38:34","modified_gmt":"2023-12-21T02:38:34","slug":"information-security-guidelines-for-investors","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/information-security-guidelines-for-investors\/","title":{"rendered":"Information Security Guidelines for Investors"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"fusion-fullwidth fullwidth-box fusion-builder-row-1 fusion-flex-container has-pattern-background has-mask-background nonhundred-percent-fullwidth non-hundred-percent-height-scrolling\" style=\"--awb-border-radius-top-left:0px;--awb-border-radius-top-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-right:0px;--awb-border-radius-bottom-left:0px;--awb-padding-top:80px;--awb-padding-bottom:80px;--awb-padding-top-medium:60px;--awb-padding-bottom-medium:60px;--awb-padding-top-small:0px;--awb-padding-bottom-small:60px;--awb-background-color:var(--awb-color1);--awb-flex-wrap:wrap;\" ><div class=\"fusion-builder-row fusion-row fusion-flex-align-items-flex-start fusion-flex-justify-content-center fusion-flex-content-wrap\" style=\"max-width:1310.4px;margin-left: calc(-4% \/ 2 );margin-right: calc(-4% \/ 2 );\"><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-0 fusion_builder_column_2_5 2_5 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:40%;--awb-margin-top-large:20px;--awb-spacing-right-large:9.6%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:4.8%;--awb-width-medium:50%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:7.68%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:7.68%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-margin-top-small:0px;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-margin-bottom-small:0px;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-1 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-bottom:16px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">What is Information and Communications Security?<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-1\"><p>As the name suggests, it means the security of information and communications. Investors engaged in online trading of securities, futures, stock subscriptions, and financial products, managing accounts, and personal investment information. Does the convenience of online execution also take into account the security of information and communication at the same time?<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-2 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">What are the Risks of Online Trading? (Risks of Electronic Trading)<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-2\"><ul>\n<li>Electronic transactions such as network transmission or telephone voice are inherently unreliable and unsafe in transmitting data.<\/li>\n<li>Transmitting data over the Internet involves risks such as interruptions and delays. (Data custody risk)<\/li>\n<li>Messages sent under someone else&#8217;s name.<\/li>\n<li>The message content is monitored remotely by others.<\/li>\n<li>The data content is stolen, altered, or damaged by others.<\/li>\n<li>The recipient denies receiving the message content, and the sender denies sending the message content.<\/li>\n<li>If the client&#8217;s personal password and electronic certificate are lost or stolen, the client shall bear the responsibility.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-3 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">What is an Electronic Certificate?<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-3\"><p>A certificate is issued by a legally authorized certification authority to confirm your identity to others. The certificate contains information that can be used to protect data or establish security when connecting to other computers. In response to the security requirements of online transactions, a comprehensive security control mechanism is provided to ensure the confidentiality, identity verification, and non-repudiation of data in online transaction services.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-4 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">What are the Security Guarantees for Using Electronic Certificates?<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-4\"><ul>\n<li>Ensures the security of each electronic transaction for investors.<\/li>\n<li>Ensures that the content of the order message will not be tampered with.<\/li>\n<li>Prevents impersonation in placing orders under false names.<\/li>\n<li>Ensures that the content of the order message will not be revealed.<\/li>\n<li>In the event of a dispute in the transaction, relevant evidence can be used as the basis for arbitration.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-5 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">When Should Certificates Be Used?<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-5\"><p>Certificates should be used when establishing transactions with securities firms and futures firms (e.g., placing orders, canceling orders, subscribing, withdrawing futures trading margins, etc.).<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><div class=\"fusion-layout-column fusion_builder_column fusion-builder-column-1 fusion_builder_column_2_5 2_5 fusion-flex-column\" style=\"--awb-bg-size:cover;--awb-width-large:40%;--awb-margin-top-large:20px;--awb-spacing-right-large:4.8%;--awb-margin-bottom-large:20px;--awb-spacing-left-large:9.6%;--awb-width-medium:50%;--awb-order-medium:0;--awb-spacing-right-medium:7.68%;--awb-spacing-left-medium:7.68%;--awb-width-small:100%;--awb-order-small:0;--awb-margin-top-small:30px;--awb-spacing-right-small:1.92%;--awb-margin-bottom-small:0px;--awb-spacing-left-small:1.92%;\"><div class=\"fusion-column-wrapper fusion-column-has-shadow fusion-flex-justify-content-flex-start fusion-content-layout-column\"><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-6 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">Online Trading Should Be Conducted through Securities and Futures Firms with Established Network Security Control Mechanisms.<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-7 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">Online Trading Security Guidelines\uff1a<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-6\"><ul>\n<li>Password Setting Principles: When setting a password, do not use easily guessable numbers such as birthdays, phone numbers, or ID numbers.<\/li>\n<li>Password Management Principles: Apply for and safeguard the electronic certificate personally (electronic certificates may be stored on media such as magnetic disks, hard drives, IC cards, etc.). Do not hand over the certificate to others for safekeeping.<\/li>\n<li>Do not disclose any personal passwords to others.<\/li>\n<li>Do not write passwords in obvious and easily accessible places.<\/li>\n<li>Change your passwords frequently and irregularly.<\/li>\n<li>Distinguish between passwords for general websites (which may be in plain text) and those for online trading to avoid being guessed or misused by others.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-8 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">Browser Usage Principles\uff1a<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-7\"><ul>\n<li>Use electronic certificates without hesitation.<\/li>\n<li>Do not allow browsers to remember personal passwords when using shared computers.<\/li>\n<li>Develop the habit of logging out of the network immediately when leaving the seat or completing a transaction.<\/li>\n<li>It is preferable not to use websites with trading functions in public places such as internet cafes.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-9 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">Handling Transaction Disputes\uff1a<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-8\"><p>Investors using electronic certificates can rely on related evidence, data, and materials as the basis for arbitration in the event of a transaction dispute.<\/p>\n<\/div><div class=\"fusion-title title fusion-title-10 fusion-sep-none fusion-title-text fusion-title-size-four\" style=\"--awb-margin-top:24px;\"><h4 class=\"fusion-title-heading title-heading-left fusion-responsive-typography-calculated\" style=\"margin:0;--fontSize:24;line-height:1.42;\">Transaction Disputes Can Be Appealed or Reported to the Following Authorities\uff1a<\/h4><\/div><div class=\"fusion-text fusion-text-9\"><ul>\n<li>Financial Supervisory Commission Securities and Futures Bureau (SFB): 886-2-8773-5100<\/li>\n<li>The Securities and Futures Investors Protection Center (SFIPC): 886-2- 2712-8899<\/li>\n<li>Taiwan Stock Exchange Corporation (TWSE): 886-2-2792-8188<\/li>\n<li>Taipei Exchange (TPEx): 886-2-2366-6100<\/li>\n<li>Taiwan Futures Exchange (TAIFEX): 886-2-2369-5678<\/li>\n<li>Other securities-related units<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"100-width.php","meta":{"footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-4876","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4876"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=4876"}],"version-history":[{"count":8,"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4876\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4990,"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/4876\/revisions\/4990"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.finroboadvisor.com\/en\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=4876"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}